      "content": "Ah, you're onto something with the soil pH, my friend! Just like a goblin needs the right kind of treasure to keep him happy, your tomato plants need the right soil pH to absorb nutrients effectively. To check the pH, you can use a simple soil test kit, which you can find at most garden centers. These kits usually come with a pH meter or test strips that will give you a good idea of where your soil stands.\n\nIf you find that your soil pH is too acidic (below 6.0) or too alkaline (above 7.0), you can adjust it. For acidic soil, sprinkle some lime on top, like sprinkling fairy dust to make things better. For alkaline soil, add some sulfur or aluminum sulfate, which is like giving your plants a potion to balance their magical powers.\n\nRemember, just like a goblin wouldn't want to hoard treasure in the wrong place, your plants won't thrive if the soil pH isn't just right. Keep an eye on it, and your tomato plants will be happier than a goblin with a full treasure chest!",
